The body of what is believed to be a fully formed foetus has been found dumped with the rubbish on Flatclay Road, a short while ago.KZN VIP received calls of the grisly find where the baby s body was wrapped in bloodstained newspaper amidst the garbage bags on the roadside. KZN VIP s Romano Naidoo and team responded immediately and were first on the scene.Members of the Rapid Response Team Phoenix (RRTP) who also responded to the scene reported that the body of the foetus had been frozen and was then dumped with the rubbish.Phoenix SAPS was contacted and further investigations will continue.There have been several incidents of foetuses dumped in various areas in Phoenix in recent weeks.Expectant mothers are urged to rather contact organisations that will assist in adoption and safe placement of newborn babies.